overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the provided statement of
  work and detailed functional specifications. The assistant performed an
  in-depth analysis, identifying several areas where the current implementation
  fell short of the requirements. A structured plan was then created,
  prioritizing the identified gaps. The first critical task undertaken was the
  integration of a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference, a key
  requirement for assessing potential safety risks. This involved modifying data
  models, updating validation rules, enhancing the user interface with a dynamic
  slider and conditional safety warnings, and ensuring these warnings were
  prominently displayed in both the interactive report and the generated PDF.
  This initial implementation successfully addressed a high-priority missing
  feature, laying the groundwork for further enhancements outlined in the plan.
